				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">1. There's a R/W pin on the CPU. When it's clocked, the pin is &quot;read&quot; and the action is done on the PPU, weather it be a read or write.<br /><br />2. The byte first goes to a buffer and is not directly read out. All reads are delayed by one. I'm not exactly sure where or how it's stored, but that's how it works.<br /><br />3. You do that by looking at the 6502 cycle-by-cycle operations for the instructions and implement them like that. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

